						<div class="postbody">All controller reading tutorials explain how you read controller and save the results as 'held' buttons. Some games seem to use 'pressed' buttons that are only '1' on the frame and go back to '0' on next frame even if the button is held. How do I implement this into the controller reading routine and which one of the two would be best to use in different situations.</div>

					
