					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">Something like a fire action would suit a newly pressed button. (Fire balls in Super Mario Bros.) Movement would work for a button that was held down. (Left or Right).<br /><br /><div class="codetitle"><b>Code:</b></div><div class="codecontent"><br />;ca65 code:<br /><br />.pushseg<br />.segment &quot;ZEROPAGE&quot;<br /><br />&nbsp; &nbsp; pressed:&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; .res&nbsp; &nbsp; 2&nbsp; &nbsp; ; new this frame - held down<br />&nbsp; &nbsp; pressedLastFrame: .res&nbsp; &nbsp; 2&nbsp; &nbsp; ; last frame / call<br />&nbsp; &nbsp; pressedNew:&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;.res&nbsp; &nbsp; 2&nbsp; &nbsp; ; newly pressed since last frame<br />&nbsp; &nbsp; releasedNew:&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; .res&nbsp; &nbsp; 2&nbsp; &nbsp; ; newly released since last frame<br /><br />.popseg<br /><br />.export&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;readPort<br />.export&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;readPort0<br />.export&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;readPort1<br /><br />.export pressed<br />.export pressedLastFrame<br />.export pressedNew<br />.export releasedNew<br /><br /><br />.proc readPort0<br />&nbsp; &nbsp; ldx #0<br />&nbsp; &nbsp; .byte $CD&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;; compare absolute, skip ldx #1<br />.endproc<br /><br />.proc readPort1<br />&nbsp; &nbsp; ldx #1<br />.endproc<br /><br />.proc readPort<br />; IN : controller to read in reg x: 0 or 1<br />; OUT: Y: ?, A: releasedNew, X: unchanged<br /><br /><br />&nbsp; &nbsp; lda pressed,x&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;; save last frame's joystick<br />&nbsp; &nbsp; sta pressedLastFrame,x<br /><br />&nbsp; &nbsp; lda #1<br />&nbsp; &nbsp; sta pressed,x&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;; set bit0 to activate carry in loop<br />&nbsp; &nbsp; sta $4016<br />&nbsp; &nbsp; lsr a&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; ; a has 0<br />&nbsp; &nbsp; sta $4016<br /><br />&nbsp; &nbsp; :<br />&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; lda $4016,x<br />&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; and #3&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;; famicom<br />&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; cmp #1&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;; friendly reads<br />&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; rol pressed,x<br />&nbsp; &nbsp; bcc :-<br /><br />&nbsp; &nbsp; ; maybe room for optimization here:&nbsp; &nbsp; <br />&nbsp; &nbsp; lda pressed,x&nbsp; <br />&nbsp; &nbsp; eor pressedLastFrame,x<br />&nbsp; &nbsp; tay<br />&nbsp; &nbsp; and pressed,x<br />&nbsp; &nbsp; sta pressedNew,x<br />&nbsp; &nbsp; tya<br />&nbsp; &nbsp; eor pressedNew,x<br />&nbsp; &nbsp; sta releasedNew,x<br />&nbsp; &nbsp; <br />&nbsp; &nbsp; rts<br />.endproc<br /></div></div>

